                <head>323. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 380th Meeting of the National Security Council, September 25, Acting
                    Director of Central Intelligence General <persName corresp="#p_CGCP1"
                        >Cabell</persName> gave the intelligence briefing on “Significant
                    Developments Affecting U.S. Security.” In his report, <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGCP1">Cabell</persName> characterized
                        <persName>Faisal</persName>’s current attitude to the United States as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In Saudi Arabia Crown Prince <persName>Faisal</persName> has taken a
                            noticeably harsher line toward the U.S. in recent conversations with the
                            U.S. Ambassador. <persName>Faisal</persName> may be considering a
                            curtailing of <gloss target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss>’s exisiting
                            rights as well as possible improvement in Saudi Arabia’s relations with
                            the <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> and the <gloss
                                target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss>.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>At the 381st Meeting of the National Security Council, October 2, Director of
                    Central Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Allen Dulles</persName> briefed
                    the Council on <persName>Faisal</persName>’s economic problems and his relations
                    with <persName corresp="#p_SAA5">Saud</persName> as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In Saudi Arabia, Crown Prince <persName>Faisal</persName> was
                            encountering a very difficult fiscal and budgetary problem. While
                                <persName>Faisal</persName> wanted to economize, King <persName
                                corresp="#p_SAA5">Saud</persName> was opposed to this course of
                            action and relations between <persName corresp="#p_SAA5">Saud</persName>
                            and <persName>Faisal</persName> appeared to be somewhat strained.”
                            (Memoranda of discussion by <persName corresp="#p_GSE1"
                                >Gleason</persName>, September 25 and October 3; Eisenhower Library,
                            Whitman File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Another extract of this meeting is printed as <ref target="#d136">Document
                        136</ref>.</p>
